## Feature Freshness

### SLA Definitions

| Feature Category | Freshness SLA | Staleness Action |
|-----------------|---------------|------------------|
| Real-time signals | < 1 minute | Use cached + warn |
| Daily aggregates | < 1 hour | Use previous day |
| Static features | < 24 hours | Use cached |
| Derived features | Same as slowest input | Compute on demand |

### Staleness Detection

```python
def check_feature_freshness(feature_name: str, max_age_seconds: int) -> bool:
    """Check if a feature is within its freshness SLA."""
    last_updated = feature_store.get_last_updated(feature_name)
    age = (datetime.utcnow() - last_updated).total_seconds()
    if age > max_age_seconds:
        logger.warning(
            "Feature stale",
            feature=feature_name,
            age_seconds=age,
            sla_seconds=max_age_seconds,
        )
        return False
    return True
```

---

## Feature Validation

### Required Checks

- [ ] No null values in required features (or documented null handling)
- [ ] Feature values within expected range (min, max, mean)
- [ ] Feature cardinality matches expectations (for categorical features)
- [ ] Feature distribution has not drifted from baseline
- [ ] Cross-feature consistency checks pass (e.g., count >= 0)

---

## Anti-Patterns

| Anti-Pattern | Why It's Bad | Correct Approach |
|--------------|--------------|------------------|
| Computing features inline during serving | Latency, inconsistency | Pre-compute and cache |
| Different code paths for train vs serve | Training/serving skew | Single feature definition |
| No freshness monitoring | Stale features degrade models | SLA monitoring |
| Unbounded feature windows | Memory explosion | Fixed-size windows |
